The paper deals with the design of stochastic local search methods for proving unsatisfiability of a constraint satisfaction problem (CSP). This falls under the broad area of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and specifically, the subfield of automated reasoning and constraint solving. The paper also involves the use of graph tensors, which are a mathematical concept used in data science (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency and parallelization of the method, which falls under the subfield of parallel and distributed computing (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves empirical evidence and experimentation, which falls under the subfield of data mining (cs.DM).
